  "prompt": "Suppose that X has a discrete uniform distribution on the integers 0 through 9. How can I determine the mean, variance, and standard deviation of the random variable Y = 5X?",
  "response": "To determine the mean, variance, and standard deviation of the random variable \\( Y = 5X \\), where \\( X \\) has a discrete uniform distribution on the integers \\( 0 \\) through \\( 9 \\), follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Understanding the Distribution of \\( X \\)\n\n- **Possible Values of \\( X \\):** \\( \\{0, 1, 2, \\ldots, 9\\} \\)\n- **Probability of Each Value:** Since \\( X \\) is uniformly distributed, each integer has an equal probability of \\( \\frac{1}{10} \\).\n\n### 2. Calculating the Mean (\\( \\mu_X \\)) of \\( X \\)\n\nThe mean of a discrete uniform distribution is given by the average of the minimum and maximum values.\n\n\\[\n\\mu_X = \\frac{a + b}{2} = \\frac{0 + 9}{2} = 4.5\n\\]\n\n### 3. Calculating the Variance (\\( \\sigma_X^2 \\)) of \\( X \\)\n\nThe variance of a discrete uniform distribution is calculated using the formula:\n\n\\[\n\\sigma_X^2 = \\frac{(n^2 - 1)}{12}\n\\]\n\nwhere \\( n \\) is the number of possible outcomes. Here, \\( n = 10 \\).\n\n\\[\n\\sigma_X^2 = \\frac{(10^2 - 1)}{12} = \\frac{99}{12} = 8.25\n\\]\n\n### 4. Determining the Mean (\\( \\mu_Y \\)) of \\( Y = 5X \\)\n\nUsing the linearity of expectation:\n\n\\[\n\\mu_Y = E(Y) = E(5X) = 5E(X) = 5 \\times 4.5 = 22.5\n\\]\n\n### 5. Determining the Variance (\\( \\sigma_Y^2 \\)) of \\( Y = 5X \\)\n\nVariance scales with the square of the constant multiplier:\n\n\\[\n\\sigma_Y^2 = \\text{Var}(Y) = \\text{Var}(5X) = 5^2 \\times \\text{Var}(X) = 25 \\times 8.25 = 206.25\n\\]\n\n### 6. Calculating the Standard Deviation (\\( \\sigma_Y \\)) of \\( Y = 5X \\)\n\nThe standard deviation is the square root of the variance:\n\n\\[\n\\sigma_Y = \\sqrt{\\sigma_Y^2} = \\sqrt{206.25} = 14.375\n\\]\n\n### **Summary**\n\n- **Mean of \\( Y \\):** \\( 22.5 \\)\n- **Variance of \\( Y \\):** \\( 206.25 \\)\n- **Standard Deviation of \\( Y \\):** \\( 14.375 \\)\n\nThese calculations provide the mean, variance, and standard deviation for the transformed random variable \\( Y = 5X \\) based on the uniform distribution of \\( X \\) from \\( 0 \\) to \\( 9 \\).",
